CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1975, pg. 13, reads: "Ms. Parks Retirement Tea - Mrs. Ernestine Parks, center, who spent many years as an educator with The Pittsburgh Board of Education, was honored recently with a gala Retirement Tea held at Centre Ave. YMCA. Others in picture, left to right are, Ms. Betty J. Williams, Pres. District 10 PTA; A. Bankston, second vice president PTSA; Ms. Lois Golden, vice principal, Schenley High; Ms. Frances Myers, president, PTSA; Andrew Parks, husband of honoree; Ms. J. Poole, first vice president of PTSA; Ms. M. Daniels, past V. P. PTSA; Ms. Agnes Davis, treasurer, PTSA and Ms. Viola Johnson, PTSA. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Betty J. Williams, A. Bankston, Lois Golden, Frances Myers, Andrew Parks, honoree Ernestine Parks, J. Poole, M. Daniels, Agnes Davis, and Viola Johnson, posed behind table for retirement tea party for Parks, at Centre Avenue YMCA
